Awesome!  I had the pork chop with fried egg and green onion with soy sauce and it was salty and tender and earthy and wonderful. So much punch in such a simple dish. The carmelization on the chop was as surprising as it was delicious.  The green onions were fresh and punchy — perfectly sautéed. The place is cute and clean and hot kitchen staff!  I can’t wait to try more. Great place!

result.adr_address: 號地舖, 15 Burd St, Sheung Wan, Hong Kong
result.formatted_address: 號地舖, 15 Burd St, Sheung Wan, Hong Kong
result.name: Yum Yum 味道 （上環）

reviews.text:
Hidden in Burd Street of Sheung Wan, Yum Yum is a cha chaan teng like restaurant that serves international cuisine, including Vietnamese, Korean, Japanese, Taiwanese, etc.

I decided to grab this Pork Chop Rice with Sunny Side Up for more protein and carbs before gym, and it was very filling indeed as the portion was huge! The pork chop is nicely pan fried with crunchy edges. Its flavor was topped up with scallion oil on top. The scallion oil actually made a good dressing for the rice too. As for the sunny side up, it’s cooked so perfectly with a nice runny egg yolk to mix the rice with. There is not a thing in this dish that’s not done perfectly.

The set also came with a complimentary hot drink. For HKD$56, it’s a very worthy set.
The pork chop here is the must try item! I love it!
